criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Undergo elective coronary angiography with at least one coronary lesion stenosis ≥
             50%;

          2. Patients with stable coronary artery diseases (stable angina, no or non-ischemic
             symptom);

          3. Written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Have prior CABG;

          2. Have stage PCI;

          3. Have no assigned scenario in Chinese appropriate use criteria.
